  "prompt": "Looking for someone who want to change his 500 and 1000 Indian notes on commision base?",
  "response": "If you're looking for someone to exchange old Indian 500 and 1000 rupee notes, it's important to be aware that these notes were demonetized in November 2016 and are no longer legal tender. The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) had set a period during which these notes could be exchanged at banks and RBI branches, but that window has long since closed.\n\nAttempting to exchange these notes through unofficial channels could be illegal and might involve risks. It's advisable to refrain from engaging in any activities that might violate local laws or regulations. If you possess these notes and have concerns, contacting a legal advisor or the relevant authorities for guidance would be a prudent approach.",
